korean:
  title: 산거
  author: 조계방
  language: kor
  text: |-
    문을 두드리는 세속 손님은 모름지기 거절하여
    이 산집의 기이한 일을 알게 하지 말라
    집 모퉁이 배꽃은 나무에 가득 피었는데
    두견새는 달 밝을 때 와서 부르짖나니
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0240_010_0560&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Mountain Dwelling
  author: Cho Gyebang
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Turn away the worldly visitor who knocks upon your door—
    let not the mysteries of this mountain home be known.
    Pear blossoms burst full upon the eaves,
    while the cuckoo calls at the moon's bright hour.
  footnotes:
    - The cuckoo (두견새) is a traditional symbol in East Asian poetry of longing, melancholy, and the voice of nature itself.
    - The mountain dwelling represents a retreat from worldly concerns and social pretense, a common theme in Korean and Chinese hermit poetry.
